cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

This paper focuses on cross-lingual correspondence between sentences and lexicons, which is a common topic in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves learning strategies and neural embedding models, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI and cs.DL (Machine Learning and Deep Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also evaluates its proposed model on two applications, including cross-lingual reverse dictionary retrieval and bilingual paraphrase identification, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language generation (cs.LG), respectively.
